\subsection{Formatting short events}

The short format fits one event on one terminal line.
It reuses [[format_header]] and [[filter_event_description]], so the only
decision here is the default for the [[week]] parameter: we default to
[[False]] because the short format is typically used in dense listings where
column width matters.
<<functions>>=
def format_event_short(event, week=False):
    """
    Takes event (icalendar.Event) object,
    returns a short string representation (one line)

    The `week` parameter is passed to the `format_header` function, it results 
    in the week number and day being included in the header. Default is 
    `False`.
    """
    header = format_header(event, week)
    description = filter_event_description(event.description)

    return f"{header} {description}".strip()
@

