\subsection{Expanding recurring events}
\label{ExpandingRecurrences}

A recurring event appears in the ICS data once, as a single
[[VEVENT]] carrying an [[RRULE]]; the individual occurrences are
implicit.
A calendar that merely stores events can leave them implicit, but
anything that \emph{displays} a date range, or computes occupied time
within one, needs the occurrences made explicit---otherwise a weekly
meeting shows up only at its first occurrence.
(This was a real defect: the [[ics]] package could not expand
recurrences at all, so external feeds---one real feed carries 227
[[RRULE]]s---lost all but the first occurrence of every recurring
event.)

Expansion must be bounded: an [[RRULE]] without an end recurs
forever, so \enquote{expand everything} does not terminate.
That is why the window is a parameter of the \emph{read} functions
rather than a post-processing step the caller might forget: the
caller that knows its date range gets correct recurrences for it, and
a caller without a range ([[window=None]]) gets the raw calendar
unchanged, never a truncated one.
The [[recurring-ical-events]] package does the actual computation;
its [[between]] returns each occurrence as a separate event (with the
occurrence's own start and end), plus the non-recurring events in
range.
<<functions>>=
def expand_recurrences(calendar, window):
  """
  Returns a new `icalendar.Calendar` with the recurring events of
  `calendar` expanded into individual occurrences within `window`, a
  (start, end) pair of datetimes. Non-recurring events within the
  window are included as they are; events outside the window are
  dropped.
  """
  start, end = window
  expanded = icalendar.Calendar()
  for event in recurring_ical_events.of(calendar).between(start, end):
    expanded.add_component(event)
  return expanded
<<imports>>=
import recurring_ical_events
@

Let's verify both behaviours with a weekly event: a window covering
three occurrences yields three events, while no window preserves the
single master event.
<<test functions>>=
def make_recurring_ics():
  return """BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//Test//Test//EN
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Weekly meeting
DTSTART:20240115T100000Z
DTEND:20240115T110000Z
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;COUNT=10
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR"""

def test_window_expands_recurrences(tmp_path):
  path = tmp_path / "recurring.ics"
  path.write_text(make_recurring_ics())
  window = (datetime.datetime(2024, 1, 15).astimezone(),
            datetime.datetime(2024, 1, 29, 23, 59).astimezone())
  cal = read_calendar(str(path), window=window)
  assert len(cal.events) == 3
  starts = sorted(event.start.date() for event in cal.events)
  assert starts == [datetime.date(2024, 1, 15),
                    datetime.date(2024, 1, 22),
                    datetime.date(2024, 1, 29)]

def test_no_window_keeps_master_event(tmp_path):
  path = tmp_path / "recurring.ics"
  path.write_text(make_recurring_ics())
  cal = read_calendar(str(path))
  assert len(cal.events) == 1
